[0.067, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[0.006, "o", "\u001b[?12l\u001b[?25h"]
[0.110, "o", "\r\u001b[KYeah — honestly, it’s a very cool little project.\r\n\r\n`pu.sh` has a lot packed into a single portable shell script:\r\n\r\n- multi-provider support: Anthropic + OpenAI\r\n- tool calling with `read`, `write`, `edit`, `grep`, `find`, `ls`, `bash`\r\n- interactive mode, pipe mode, history, logging\r\n- local project context loading\r\n- resumable memory\r\n- compaction when context gets too large\r\n- API error handling/retry logic\r\n- cost/token tracking hooks\r\n- self-setup/login flow\r\n- no heavyweight runtime dependency beyond shell + curl + awk\r\n\r\nThat’s an impressive amount of agent harness in ~400 lines of shell.\r\n\r\nThe scary/fun part is that it’s doing JSON parsing, API protocol handling, process control, history management, compaction, and file-edit tooling in POSIX-ish shell. So yes: awesome, but also exactly the kind of thing where weird edge cases can hide. Which is good — plenty of fun bugs to hunt.\r\n"]
[0.064, "o", "\r\u001b[K\u001b[36m[pu]\u001b[0m done · ~/Documents/code/pu (main) ↑55k ↓612 17.3%/400k (openai) gpt-5.5 • medium\r\n"]
